    • Uses of Collector in uml_parser.collectors

      Subclasses of Collector in uml_parser.collectors 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  AggregationCollector
      This class collects an Aggregation which correspond to 'AGGREGATION' 'CONTAINER' 'PARTS' ; (with/without spaces).
      class  AssociationCollector
      This class collects an Association which correspond to 'RELATION''ROLES',; (with/without spaces).
      class  ClassContentCollector
      This class collects an Operation which correspond to (): (with/without spaces).
      class  DataitemCollector
      This class collects a Dataitem which correspond to : (with/without spaces).
      class  DataitemListCollector
      This class collects a DataitemList which correspond to [{,}] (with/without spaces).
      class  GeneralizationCollector
      This class collects a Generalization which correspond to 'GENERALIZATION''SUBCLASSES'; (with/without spaces).
      class  IdentifierListCollector
      This class collects a list of identifiers which correspond to [{,}] (with/without spaces).
      class  ModelCollector
      This class collects a mix of ClassContentCollector, AssociationCollector, GeneralizationCollector and AggregationCollector declarations and use them to represent a UML schema.
      class  OperationCollector
      This class collects an Operation which correspond to (): (with/without spaces).
      class  OperationListCollector
      This class collects a Dataitem which correspond to : (with/without spaces).
      class  RoleCollector
      This class collects a Dataitem which correspond to : (with/without spaces).
      class  RoleListCollector
      This class collects a RoleList which correspond to {,} (with/without spaces).
      Methods in uml_parser.collectors with parameters of type Collector 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void RoleListCollector.addChild(Collector collector, int index)
      Expects 0+ RoleCollector's and puts each, in order, in a list.
      void RoleCollector.addChild(Collector collector, int index)
      Expects two StringCollector's, the first one (index = 0) being the identifier, the second one (index = 1) being the multiplicity.
      void OperationListCollector.addChild(Collector collector, int index)
      Expects two StringCollector's, the first one (index = 0) being the identifier, the second one (index = 1) being the multiplicity.
      void OperationCollector.addChild(Collector collector, int index)
      Expects two StringCollector's, the first one (index = 0) being the identifier, the second one (index = 1) being the multiplicity, and also expects one DataitemListCollector containing 0+ Dataitem.
      void ModelCollector.addChild(Collector collector, int index)
      Expects one StringCollector containing the identifier (name) of the model and any of ClassContentCollector, AssociationCollector, GeneralizationCollector and AggregationCollector.
      void IdentifierListCollector.addChild(Collector collector, int index)
      Expects 0+ StringCollector's, each being an identifier.
      void GeneralizationCollector.addChild(Collector collector, int index)
      Expects one StringCollector being the identifier, and one IdentifierListCollector which contains the names (identifiers) of the subclasses.
      void DataitemListCollector.addChild(Collector collector, int index)
      Expects 0+ DataitemCollector's and puts each, in order, in a list.
      void DataitemCollector.addChild(Collector collector, int index)
      Expects two StringCollector's, the first one (index = 0) being the identifier, the second one (index = 1) being the type.
      void ClassContentCollector.addChild(Collector collector, int index)
      Expects two StringCollector's, the first one (index = 0) being the identifier, the second one (index = 1) being the multiplicity, and also expects one DataitemListCollector containing 0+ Dataitem.
      void AssociationCollector.addChild(Collector collector, int index)
      Expects two StringCollector's, the first one (index = 0) being the identifier, the second one (index = 1) being the multiplicity, and also expects one DataitemListCollector containing 0+ Dataitem.
      void AggregationCollector.addChild(Collector collector, int index)
      Expects one RoleCollector being the "owner" of the parts, and one RoleListCollector being the parts of the aggregation.
